        <num>CCP 3863</num>
        <heading>3863.  Person against whom writ directed</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3863.  Person against whom writ directed
A writ of mandamus may be directed to a public officer to compel the performance of a ministerial duty required by law, or to a former officer or his heirs to compel the delivery of the papers and effects of the office to his successor.</p>
        </content>
